its special\nmeaning to all g o o d Americans\nand concluded her part of the pro\ngram by giving a \u201cchalk talk\u201d\non the symbolism represented by\nour flag. Patriotic music was\nplayed by Mrs. Han Jensen.\nA delightful lunch was served\nby the hostesses of the evening,\nMrs. Tex Hughes, Mrs. Tom\nRodgers and Mrs. Wilbur Ren\nshaw and a pleasant social hour\nwas enjoyed by all.\nHim\nNEW LEG ROOM Real stretch-out room\nfor long legs and tall people and Dodge\n\u201cknee-level\u201d seals give them full support for\ncomfortable and relaxing day-long trips.\nand more head room plus the amazingly\nR-m-o-o-t-b ride of Dodge All-Fluid Drive.\nNew styling new \"Get-Away\u201d engine new\nluxury ano coinfort optional Gyro-Matic\ntransmission are only a few of the new things\nthat\u2019ll thrill you. But see them all at your Dodge\ndealer\u2019s now. Learn first hand just what the\ndaring new Dodge will do for you.\nOn U.\u201eS. Highway\nNo. 2\nwI\nZ STYLE\nMillion, of American, are >avln, bUTion.\nof dollars in their bank accounts for\nold age i for things they want. I. for\nemergencies for lean years that may\nlie ahead. Save now, while you are earning\nmore. Grasp this opportunity to get ahead\nfinancially. SAVE jll SAVE SAVE\nThe First National Bank\nof Browning fl\nDesignated Depository of Indian Funds U\nMember Federal Deposit Insurance .Corporation fl\nAT THIS BANK=J\nAssembly of God\nSunday School at 10 a. m.\nWorship at 11 a. m.\nEvening revival hour at 8.\nWednesday Bible study at 8.\nCordial invitation to everyone.\nRev. R. A. Murphey, pastor.\nTimber Management\nProperly spaced forest trees will\ngrow high quality lumber more\nquickly. Trees too close together\nslow down in growth. Trees too far\napart will produce big limbs and\npoor lumber.\nSSS\nNEW PERFORMANCE New \u201cGet-Away\u201d en\ngine, plus Fluid Drive, squeezes extra miles\nfrom every tankful of gas gives you much\nfaster acceleration for safer passing.\nBrowning, Mont.\nMethodist Church\n